        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 23 at 8:03PM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 803 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of J B Thomas Reservoir, or 11 miles west of Snyder,
moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Big Spring, Snyder, Ackerly, Gail, Fluvanna, J B Thomas Reservoir,
Luther, Sparenberg, Vincent, Hermleigh, Randalls Corner, Winston
Field, Cuthbert, Knapp, Dunn, Knott, Ira, and Vealmoor.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
